---
import SectionHeading from "../ui/SectionHeading.astro";
---

<section class="safe-x border-y border-border bg-card py-16 lg:py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto grid w-full max-w-6xl items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <div>
      <SectionHeading align="left" kicker="The manufacturing wedge" title="Assemblies inside assemblies" />
      <p class="mt-5 text-muted-foreground">
        Most tools at this weight class stop at single-level kits. Stocklore builds the whole tree: confirm a sale for a finished product and it creates the
        manufacturing orders for every sub-assembly underneath, consumes components bottom-up, and records every movement in the stock ledger.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-muted-foreground">That's the kind of depth others reserve for their upper tiers — here it's just how the product works.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Real nested lists — the diagram is its own accessible description -->
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-background p-5 shadow-soft">
      <p class="pb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">One confirmed sale becomes</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm">
        <li>
          <div class="rounded-md border border-primary/50 bg-lightest/50 px-4 py-2.5 font-semibold">Manufacturing order — Garden Bench × 10</div>
          <ul class="ml-5 mt-1.5 space-y-1.5 border-l-2 border-border pl-4">
            <li>
              <div class="rounded-md border border-border bg-card px-4 py-2 font-medium">Sub-order — Seat assembly × 10</div>
              <ul class="ml-5 mt-1.5 space-y-1 border-l-2 border-border pl-4 text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Consumes: Oak slats × 40</li>
                <li>Consumes: Wood finish × 2 L</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <div class="rounded-md border border-border bg-card px-4 py-2 font-medium">Sub-order — Frame assembly × 10</div>
              <ul class="ml-5 mt-1.5 space-y-1 border-l-2 border-border pl-4 text-muted-foreground">
                <li>Consumes: Steel legs × 20</li>
                <li>Consumes: Bolts M8 × 80</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 border-t border-border pt-3 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
        Sub-assemblies nest up to 6 levels deep. Completion consumes components bottom-up and yields the finished good — every leg on the ledger.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
